        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think `'messagesheight'` should not be a number, but a value with a default akin to `cmd:0.5,dialog:0.5,msg:0.5,pager:1`, mirroring how the current config is structured now. That way heights for each type of window remain able to be configured individually (perhaps some could be merged into a single name if it seems justified).\n\nUsing `'mopt'` for most other settings seems fair. Other dedicated options could be introduced for anything else that's important.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-27T01:44:50Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38445#issuecomment-4139483084",
